'''Catagenesis''' is a somewhat archaic term from [[evolutionary biology]] referring to evolutionary directions that were considered "[[wiktionary:retrogressive|retrogressive]]."  It was a term used in contrast to [[anagenesis]], which in present usage denotes the evolution of a single population into a new form without branching lines of descent.

